              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="description-1" class="problem-description">
            <div class="problem-description-text">
              <p>
                In a radial drilling machine, accurately determining the depth
                of the hole while drilling can be challenging. The goal is to
                develop an attachment that can be added to the existing radial
                drilling machine, enabling it to semi-automatically control and
                monitor the drilling depth, ensuring precise results with less
                manual intervention.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button class="btn btn-secondary action-button">Continue</button>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item" id="problem-2">
          <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
            <div class="d-flex align-items-center">
              <span class="problem-number">2</span>
              <span class="problem-title">Child Safety Monitoring System</span>
            </div>
            <button
              class="btn btn-primary btn-sm"
              onclick="toggleDescription(2)"
            >
              Start
            </button>
          </div>
          <div id="description-2" class="problem-description">
            <div class="problem-description-text">
              <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Company Challenge:</h6>
              <p>
                Parents today are increasingly concerned about the safety and
                well-being of their children, especially regarding school
                attendance and safety during playtime in designated areas. We
                are seeking innovative proposals for a system that can track a
                child&apos;s school attendance and monitor their location during
                play. The system should feature:
              </p>

              <h6 class="fw-bold">Boundary Alert System:</h6>
              <p>
                Define a specific safety boundary (e.g., 100 meters) around the
                child&apos;s play area, with an alert system that notifies
                parents if the child crosses this boundary.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Parental Notifications:</h6>
              <p>
                Real-time alerts should be sent to parents via a mobile app or
                SMS, informing them if the child misses school or leaves the
                designated play area.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Mobile App/Web Dashboard:</h6>
              <p>
                A user-friendly mobile app for parents to receive alerts and
                track their child&apos;s attendance and location, along with a
                detailed web dashboard that provides comprehensive reports and
                settings.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Emergency Contact Integration:</h6>
              <p>
                Include an emergency contact feature within the app, allowing
                parents to respond quickly to alerts or emergencies.
              </p>
              <p>
                Additionally, the solution must ensure full compliance with
                privacy laws and regulations regarding children&apos;s data,
                implement strong security measures to protect sensitive
                information, and provide clear communication to parents
                regarding the system&apos;s purpose and functionality.
              </p>
              <p>
                We challenge innovators to create a robust, scalable, and secure
                system that addresses these key safety and tracking concerns,
                providing peace of mind to parents and guardians.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button class="btn btn-secondary action-button">Continue</button>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item" id="problem-3">
          <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
            <div class="d-flex align-items-center">
              <span class="problem-number">3</span>
              <span class="problem-title"
                >Vehical and Smart Home Management Integration</span
              >
              <span>| IoT</span>
            </div>
            <button
              class="btn btn-primary btn-sm"
              onclick="toggleDescription(3)"
            >
              Start
            </button>
          </div>
          <div id="description-3" class="problem-description">
            <div class="problem-description-text">
              <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Company Challenge:</h6>
              <p>
                We are looking to create a seamless and intuitive experience
                where users can remotely manage their smart home devices simply
                by interacting with their vehicle's voice assistant. This
                innovation should offer a smooth transition between automotive
                control and home automation, enhancing convenience, safety, and
                functionality for users on the go.
              </p>

              <h5 class="fw-bold">Key Features to Address:</h5>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Cross-Domain Voice Command Integration:</h6>
              <p>
                Develop a system that allows users to issue voice commands not
                only for vehicular control but also for managing various smart
                home devices, such as lighting, climate control, and
                entertainment systems.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Home Automation Connectivity:</h6>
              <p>
                Establish a strong and reliable connection between the car's
                voice assistant and the user's smart home devices, enabling
                users to control a variety of home automation functions
                remotely.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Natural Language Understanding:</h6>
              <p>
                Implement advanced natural language processing algorithms to
                ensure the voice assistant can accurately understand and process
                user commands related to both vehicle and home control
                seamlessly.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Secure Authentication:</h6>
              <p>
                Integrate secure authentication measures to verify the user's
                identity and prevent unauthorized access to home devices through
                voice commands, ensuring privacy and security.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Device-Specific Commands:</h6>
              <p>
                Enable users to issue commands specific to individual devices,
                such as adjusting thermostats, turning lights on/off, or
                controlling entertainment systems, via voice commands.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Remote Monitoring:</h6>
              <p>
                Provide users the ability to check the status of their home
                devices through voice queries while driving, ensuring peace of
                mind and efficient management of their smart home.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Integration with Smart Home Platforms:</h6>
              <p>
                Ensure compatibility with popular smart home platforms like
                Google Home and Amazon Alexa, which will extend the system's
                functionality and support a broader range of devices.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Contextual Understanding:</h6>
              <p>
                Develop the system's ability to understand contextual
                information, such as user location or time of day, to offer more
                natural and tailored voice interactions (e.g., adjusting
                temperature based on proximity or weather).
              </p>
              <h5 class="fw-bold">Considerations for Solution Design:</h5>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Privacy Protection:</h6>
              <p>
                Ensure robust privacy measures to protect user data, including
                secure communication channels between the car's voice assistant
                and smart home devices, and prevent unauthorized access.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Device Compatibility:</h6>
              <p>
                The solution should support a wide variety of smart home
                devices, ensuring that it works seamlessly across diverse user
                setups and preferences.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">User-Friendly Experience:</h6>
              <p>
                Design an intuitive and user-friendly interface that provides
                clear feedback on voice command execution, with easy navigation
                and real-time control for a seamless experience.
              </p>

              <p>
                We invite innovators to propose a solution that integrates
                vehicle voice assistants with smart home management, ensuring a
                secure, efficient, and user-friendly experience that enhances
                both automotive and home automation functionalities.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button class="btn btn-secondary action-button">Continue</button>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item" id="problem-4">
          <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
            <div class="d-flex align-items-center">
              <span class="problem-number">4</span>
              <span class="problem-title"
                >Machine Support and Packaging Solution</span
              >
              <span>| Packaging</span>
            </div>
            <button
              class="btn btn-primary btn-sm"
              onclick="toggleDescription(4)"
            >
              Start
            </button>
          </div>
          <div id="description-4" class="problem-description">
            <div class="problem-description-text">
              <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Company Challenge:</h6>
              <p>
                We are facing a decrease in the service life of our machines due
                to the lack of support at one end. The challenge is to design a
                solution that provides support to the machine while ensuring
                that it is functional and efficient in handling bottles during
                transport and filling. The solution should address the following
                key requirements:
              </p>

              <h5 class="fw-bold">Key Features to Address:</h5>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Bearing Support:</h6>
              <p>
                Design a bearing to be installed at one end of the machine to
                provide additional support, preventing premature wear and
                extending the service life of the equipment.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Reusability:</h6>
              <p>
                The bearing support system should be reusable, ensuring
                long-term durability and cost-effectiveness for ongoing
                operations.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Ease of Bottle Handling:</h6>
              <p>
                The solution should facilitate the easy removal of bottles from
                their packing without causing damage to the bottles or packaging
                materials.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Government Compliance for Packaging:</h6>
              <p>
                Ensure that the packaging material used for the bottles complies
                with relevant government regulations and environmental
                standards, avoiding any non-compliant materials.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Returnable Packaging:</h6>
              <p>
                If heavy commercial vehicles are used to transport bottles to
                the filling station, the packaging material should be designed
                to be returned to the production plant for reuse, minimizing
                waste and promoting sustainability.
              </p>
              <h5 class="fw-bold">Considerations for Solution Design:</h5>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Durability and Strength:</h6>
              <p>
                The bearing and packaging solutions must be designed to
                withstand the demands of heavy-duty operations, ensuring that
                both support and packaging materials last over time.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Environmental Impact:</h6>
              <p>
                Focus on reducing environmental impact by using recyclable and
                reusable materials for packaging, ensuring compliance with
                sustainability goals and regulations.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Cost Efficiency:</h6>
              <p>
                The solution should be cost-effective both in terms of initial
                investment and long-term operational savings, considering the
                reusability and durability of the components.
              </p>

              <p>
                We challenge innovators to develop a solution that enhances
                machine longevity, supports efficient bottle handling, and
                ensures compliance with regulatory standards while addressing
                sustainability and operational efficiency.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button class="btn btn-secondary action-button">Continue</button>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item" id="problem-5">
          <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
            <div class="d-flex align-items-center">
              <span class="problem-number">5</span>
              <span class="problem-title"
