          <div id="description-6" class="problem-description">
            <div class="problem-description-text">
              <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Company Challenge:</h6>
              <p>
                Currently, the traditional method of packing bottles involves
                using a cover to secure a stack of bottles for transportation
                from the production plant to the filling station. However, once
                the cover is removed at the filling station, it is often torn
                and cannot be reused. Wooden boxes are not a viable option due
                to the high cost of transporting them back. We are seeking an
                innovative, sustainable packing solution that satisfies the
                following key constraints:
              </p>

              <h6 class="fw-bold">Key Requirements:</h6>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Reusability:</h6>
              <p>
                The new packing solution must be reusable, reducing waste and
                improving cost-efficiency over multiple transportation cycles.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Ease of Bottle Handling:</h6>
              <p>
                The packaging should be designed in a way that makes it easy to
                remove bottles without damaging the packaging or the bottles
                themselves.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Government Compliance:</h6>
              <p>
                Ensure that the packing material used complies with all relevant
                government regulations and environmental standards, avoiding
                non-compliant materials.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Returnable Packaging:</h6>
              <p>
                If heavy commercial vehicles are used to transport bottles to
                the filling station, the packaging material must be designed to
                be easily returned to the production plant, reducing waste and
                transportation costs.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Considerations for Solution Design:</h6>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Durability and Strength:</h6>
              <p>
                The packaging should be durable enough to withstand
                transportation, while still being lightweight to optimize
                shipping costs.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Environmental Impact:</h6>
              <p>
                Prioritize eco-friendly materials that are recyclable,
                biodegradable, or reusable to minimize the environmental
                footprint.
              </p>
              <h6 class="fw-bold">Cost Efficiency:</h6>
              <p>
                The solution should balance both the initial investment and the
                long-term cost savings through reusability and reduced waste.
              </p>

              <p>
                We challenge innovators to design a packaging solution that
                balances sustainability, ease of use, and compliance with
                regulatory standards, while offering an efficient and
                cost-effective solution for both transportation and reuse.
              </p>
            </div>
            <button class="btn btn-secondary action-button">Continue</button>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item" id="problem-7">
